
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `namei` baraye taghir dadan ya namayesh dadan etela'at karbari (user information) dar system estefade mishavad. In etela'at mesle name kamel va etela'ate rabete karbar ast.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `namei -u username` --> 👤 Taghir dadan etela'at karbari moshakhas ba username
    🔹 `namei -n "Full Name"` --> 📝 Taghir dadan name kamel karbar
    🔹 `namei -r "Room Number"` --> 🏢 Taghir dadan ya ezafe kardan shomare otagh karbar.
    🔹 `namei` --> 👀 Namayesh etela'ate karbare fa'al. (bi hich gozine)

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ namei -n "Ali Rezaei"

    🔹 Taghir name kamel karbare fa'al be "Ali Rezaei".

    $ namei -u john -r "Office 202"

    🔹 Taghir shomare otagh karbar "john" be "Office 202".

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ namei

    🔹 Namayesh etela'ate karbare fa'al. Output mesle name kamel, shomare otagh va etela'ate digar neshan dade mishavad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `namei` command is used to change or display user information on the system. This includes the user's full name and contact information.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `namei -u username` --> 👤 Modify information for a specific user with username.
    🔹 `namei -n "Full Name"` --> 📝 Change the user's full name.
    🔹 `namei -r "Room Number"` --> 🏢 Change or add the user's room number.
    🔹 `namei` --> 👀 Display the information of the current user (without any options).

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ namei -n "Ali Rezaei"

    🔹 Changes the full name of the current user to "Ali Rezaei".

    $ namei -u john -r "Office 202"

    🔹 Changes the room number of user "john" to "Office 202".

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ namei

    🔹 Displays the information of the current user.  The output shows the full name, room number, and other details.
